MIKE AND ADEENA’S EXCELLENT ISRAELI ADVENTURE - NOV 30 - DEC 8, 2023. 

We love nothing more than eating our way through Israel together, and now we’re inviting you to come along for the ride. Between November 30 - December 8th, join us and @viasabra as we guide you through the best eating experiences Israel has to offer, meeting friends, experts, and personalities you can only find in Israel. 

You’ll get to ask us your burning Israeli food questions and schmooze, cook, and snack with us every day until the sun goes down (and then some). Expect delicious surprises including amazing outdoor meals, concerts, and a magical candle-lighting for the first night of Chanukah. 

Visit Viasabra.com to register - early bird special available. See you soon!

Cook with Us! I had the immense privilege to join PA @governorshapiro and First Lady Lori at the Governor’s Residence again – this time with my friend and Philly’s own @chefjosegarces for the Feast and Fitness initiative. As members of the President’s Council on Sports, Fitness, and Nutrition - Chef Jose and I are throwing a cook along to get into the Thanksgiving spirit. We’re making brussels sprouts, corn humitas AND the First Lady’s sugared pecans, and talking about ways to stay active this holiday season. We’re also joined by fellow council member the great Ben Jacobs, who joins us to discuss Native American Heritage Month and traditions, and ingredients from his community. Register online today and we’ll see you on Zoom THIS MONDAY, NOV 13TH at 6pm ET! Link in my bio to register.

I am beyond grateful to @governorshapiro and First Lady Lori Shapiro for welcoming me and @chefjosegarces to the Governor’s Residence on behalf of the President’s Council on Sports, Fitness & Nutrition. We made three Thanksgiving dishes, including Jose’s incredible humitas, the Shapiro’s infamous candied pecans, which you HAVE TO TRY! We had the incredible opportunity to chat with friend and Council Member Chef Ben Jacobs about Native American Heritage Month and his community’s traditions and native dishes. This is the legendary @zahavrestaurant Lamb Shoulder, which has  been their signature dish for more than 12 years. The process takes three days to complete 🤯 (but only an hour in the oven for you!).
